1. *Činjenica* da su ljudi sve više vezani za mobilne telefone postaje zabrinjavajuća. (The fact that people are increasingly attached to mobile phones is becoming worrisome.)
2. Upravo sam saznala *činjenicu* da će sutra biti kiša. (I just found out the fact that it will rain tomorrow.)
3. Oni osporavaju *činjenicu* da je ova informacija tačna. (They dispute the fact that this information is correct.)
4. Kako se nositi sa *činjenicom* da su cene hrane sve veće? (How to deal with the fact that food prices are increasing?)
5. Moramo prihvatiti *činjenicu* da smo napravili grešku. (We must accept the fact that we made a mistake.)
6. U ovom tekstu se navodi *činjenica* da su ljudi sve manje fizički aktivni. (This text states the fact that people are becoming less physically active.)
7. Šta je *činjenica* koju svi znamo o globalnom zagrevanju? (What is the fact that we all know about global warming?)
8. *Činjenica* da ste preduzeli sve moguće korake da se ovo reši je ohrabrujuća. (The fact that you have taken all possible steps to resolve this is encouraging.)
9. Oni ne shvataju *činjenicu* da njihove reakcije imaju posledice. (They don't realize the fact that their reactions have consequences.)
10. Kako bi *činjenica* da su neki ljudi uspešniji od nas mogla da nas motiviše? (How can the fact that some people are more successful than us motivate us?)